quare Media}}\n\n{{coord|33|11|17|N|87|35|23|W|type:landmark_region:US|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Radio stations in Alabama|TSK]]\n[[Category:Gospel radio stations in the United States]]\n[[Category:Radio stations established in 1984]]\n[[Category:Townsquare Media radio stations]]\n\n\n{{Alabama-radio-station-stub}}\n{{Christian-radio-station-stub}}\n", "name_user": "12.218.138.194", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WTSK"}
{"title_page": "Super 30 (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 Indian Hindi-language biographical film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Super 30\n| image          = Super 30 The Film.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = {{ubl|[[Vikas Bahl]]}}\n| producer       = {{ubl|[[Phantom Films]]|[[Nadiadwala Grandson Entertainment]]|[[Reliance Entertainment]]}}\n| starring       = {{ubl|[[Hrithik Roshan]]|[[Mrunal Thakur]]|[[Virendra Saxena]]|[[Pankaj Tripathi]]|[[Aditya Srivastava]]|[[Amit Sadh]]}}\n| writer         = Sanjeev Dutta\n| based on  = [[Anand Kumar]]\n| music          = [[Ajay\u2212Atul]]\n| cinematography = [[Anay Goswamy]]\n| editing        = [[A. Sreekar Prasad]]\n| studio         = {{ubl|[[Phantom Films]]|[[Nadiadwala Grandson Entertainment]]|[[Reliance Entertainment]]|HRX Films}}\n| distributor    = [[Reliance Entertainment]]<br>[[PVR Pictures]]\n| country        = India\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|07|12|df=y|}}\n| runtime        = 155 minutes<ref name=\"bbfc\">{{Citation |url=https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/super-30-2019 |title=Super 30 |publisher=[[British Board of Film Classification]] |access-date=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n| language       = Hindi\n| budget         = {{INR|link=yes}}60 [[crore]]<ref name=\"budget\">{{cite web |title=Super 30: Hrithik Roshan Starrer Is Made At THIS Budget & Not 110 Or 120 Crores? |url=https://www.koimoi.com/box-office/super-30-hrithik-roshan-starrer-is-made-at-this-budget-not-110-or-120-crores/ |website=www.koimoi.com |publisher=Koimoi |accessdate=13 August 2019}}</ref>\n| gross          =  {{INR}}208.93 crore<ref name=\"boxtop\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/super-30/box-office/|title=Super 30 Box Office|website=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|accessdate=14 August 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"boxtg\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/box-office-collections/worldwide/2019/|title=Bollywood Top Grossers Worldwide Bollywood Hungama|access-date=15 August 2019|website=[[Bollywood Hungama]]}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Super 30''''' is a 2019 Indian [[Hindi]]-language [[biographical film|biographical]] [[drama film]] directed by [[Vikas Bahl]] and co-produced by [[Sajid Nadiadwala]] on a budget of {{INRConvert|60|c}}, narrating the life of mathematician [[Anand Kumar]] and his  [[Super 30|educational program of the same name]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/super-30-first-look-anand-kumar-says-hrithik-roshans-resemblance-to-him-is-uncanny-4340299.html|title=Super 30 first look: Anand Kumar says Hrithik Roshan's resemblance to him is 'uncanny'|publisher=Firstpost|date=7 February 2018|accessdate=9 February 2018}}</ref> Co-distributed by [[Reliance Entertainment]], the film stars [[Hrithik Roshan]] as Anand, with [[Mrunal Thakur]], [[Virendra Saxena]], [[Pankaj Tripathi]], [[Aditya Srivastava]], Nandish Singh, Aayush Kumar Shukla and [[Amit Sadh]] in supporting roles.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/photo-features/most-talked-about-biopics-you-just-cannot-miss/super-30-first-look-hrithik-roshan-looks-convincing-as-he-steps-into-math-genius-anand-kumars-shoes/photostory/62801512.cms|title=Most talked about biopics you just cannot miss|work=The Times of India|date=8 February 2018|accessdate=9 February 2018}}</ref> \n\n''Super 30'' was Phantom Film's last production.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/anurag-kashyap-partners-dissolve-of-phantom-films-of-queen-udta-punjab-fame-super-30-to-be-banners-last-1900411.html|title=Phantom Films Dissolved, Vikas Bahl's Super 30 will be Banner's Last Film|work=News18|access-date=2018-11-19}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/hrithik-roshans-super-30-actress-mrunal-thakur-spotted-on-set-see-pics-1810560|title=Hrithik Roshan's Super 30: Actress Mrunal Thakur Spotted On Set. See Pics|last=Shiksha|first=Shruti|publisher=NDTV|date=|accessdate=9 February 2018}}</ref> [[Principal photography]] began in February 2018 and the film was extensively shot in Ramnagar Fort and [[Sambhar Lake Town]] which was shown as [[Kota, Rajasthan]].<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite news|url=http://ahmedabadmirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/discovery-of-india/articleshow/63356801.cms|title=From Meghna Gulzar to Vikas Bahl, filmmakers explore the untapped interiors of India|last=Iyer|first=Sanyukta|work=Mumbai Mirror|date=19 March 2018|accessdate=25 March 2018}}</ref> ''Super 30'' was theatrically released in India on 12 July 2019 and received positive to mixed reviews, but with some praise for the storyline and Roshan's performance.<ref name=\":cr2\"/><ref name=\"boxtg\"/> With worldwide earnings of {{INRConvert|208.93|c}}, the film emerged as one of the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing Indian films]]. Based on domestic net collection, the film stands among top 40 in the list of [[List of highest domestic net collection of Hindi films|Hindi films with highest India net collection]] with a lifetime [[net income|net]] gross of {{INRConvert|146.95|c}} in India.\n\n==Plot==\n\n[[Anand Kumar]] is a lower-class student who has a passion in studies and is good at it. At a local competition felicitation, the local minister, Shriram Singh, proud of him, promises for help whenever needed.\n\nAnand frequently goes to Banaras Hindu University's library to solve a foreign Math journal. One day, the manager finally catches him, and says that he has no right to read there. One staff member suggests him to get his article published in this journal and earn a free lifetime subscription to it. Anand goes to the post-office, where his father Rajendra works as the head, and posts a letter regarding the solution to a difficult Math problem that no one has been able to solve yet. He then gets featured in the journal for solving the problem, and gets a letter from Professor Richard of the [[University of Cambridge]] to join a program there. But Anand needs money to travel. He and Rajendra go to Shriram but he denies any promise. They both further try to collect money but remain helpless, and get depressed. One day, Rajendra dies of a heart attack. Anand refuses to go to Cambridge due to his father's death and financial condition.\n\nHe then sells [[Papadum|papads]] in the city. One day, he meets Lallan Singh, an assistant of the local minister. Lallan takes Anand as a teacher in his coaching centre, Excellence Coaching Centre. There, Anand sees the plight of a boy who had to leave due to poverty. He thinks that these poor kids also have a right to study. Hence, he leaves Excellence and starts a separate tuition for poor kids, in which he enrolls 30 kids at a time. He teaches them to learn everything practically and have the concepts cleared in an easy and fun way. All this enrages Lallan, whose centre is facing criticism for not retaining Anand.\n\nIn course of the tuition, Anand gets immense help from his brother Pranav and his mother. Lallan and Shriram plan to have Anand killed so that his kids won't be entering [[Indian Institutes of Technology|IIT]]. Anand is hurt brutally by two of Lallan's henchmen, and is hospitalised, on the verge of death. He tells his students to then use their knowledge to defeat the goons sent by Shriram, while he is being treated. The students, in unity, use their knowledge and defeat the goons and Anand is treated successfully. The students take the IIT exam and all 30 students pass successfully.\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Hrithik Roshan]] as [[Anand Kumar]], a [[Mathematician|mathematician]] who opens a program named Super 30 where he teaches 30 students for [[Indian Institutes of Technology|IIT]] in free cost.\n* [[Mrunal Thakur]] as Supriya, Anand's love interest.\n* [[Virendra Saxena]] as Rajendra Kumar,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/on-sets-hrithik-roshan-loses-weight-for-his-role-in-super-30/19433190|title=On sets: Hrithik Roshan loses weight for his role in Super 30|date=2018-05-18|work=mid-day|access-date=2018-08-09|language=en}}</ref> Anand's father who dies after suffering from a heart attack.\n* [[Nandish Sandhu|Nandish Singh]] as Pranav Kumar,<ref>{{cite web|title=Meet Nandish Singh, who plays Hrithik Roshan's brother in 'Super 30'|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-meet-nandish-singh-who-plays-hrithik-roshan-s-brother-in-super-30-2589947|website=dnaindia.com|date=2 March 2018|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref> Anand's brother.\n* [[Aditya Shrivastava]] as Lallan Singh, Shri Ram's assistant.\n* [[Sadhana Singh]] as Jayanti Kumar, Anand's mother.\n* [[Pankaj Tripathi]] as Shri Ram Singh,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-pankaj-tripathi-to-play-hrithik-roshan-aka-anand-kumar-s-arch-rival-in-super-30-2625091|title=Pankaj Tripathi to play Hrithik Roshan aka Anand Kumar's arch-rival in Super 30|date=2018-06-13|work=dna|access-date=2018-08-09|language=en-US}}</ref> a local minister.\n*[[Vijay Varma]] as Fugga Kumar\n* [[Amit Sadh]] as Raghunath<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/amit-sadh-is-super-30s-sutradhar/articleshow/64753466.cms|title=Amit Sadh is the narrator for Hrithik Roshan-starrer Super 30|work=Mumbai Mirror|access-date=2018-08-09}}</ref>\n*Sharat Sonu as Haadim Malik, Shriram's secretary.\n*[[Manav Gohil]] as Purushottam\n*Aayush Kumar Shukla as Vinod\n*[[Rahul Raj]] as Kishore\n*Deepali Gautam as Kusum\n*[[Ali Haji (actor)|Ali Haji]] as Prithvi\n*[[Rajesh Sharma (actor)|Rajesh Sharma]] as Bachchi\n*[[Karishma Sharma]] in [[item number]] \"Paisa\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.desimartini.com/news/martini-shots/breakdowns/super-30s-paisa-song-hrithik-roshan-shows-the-power-money-can-give-article112078.htm|title=Super 30\u2019s Paisa Song: Hrithik Roshan Shows The Power Money Can Give!|date=21 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/super-30-new-song-paisa-hrithik-roshan-as-anand-kumar-shows-importance-of-money-1553307-2019-06-21|title=Super 30 new song Paisa: Hrithik Roshan as Anand Kumar shows importance of money|date=22 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n[[Mrunal Thakur]] was cast opposite Hrithik Roshan in the film. The film was shot at [[Ramnagar Fort]]; part of the fort was converted to look like the Super 30 institute.<ref name=\":p1\">{{cite news|url=http://www.news18.com/news/movies/super-30-kumkum-bhagya-star-mrunal-thakur-to-play-hrithik-roshan-love-interest-in-the-film-1655299.html|title=Super 30: Kumkum Bhagya Star Mrunal Thakur To Play Hrithik Roshan's Love Interest In The Film?|publisher=CNN-News 18|date=9 February 2018|accessdate=9 February 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\"/> The film was also shot for ten days in [[Sambhar Lake Town]] which was shown as [[Kota, Rajasthan]] and Jaipur.<ref name=\"auto\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/hrithik-roshan-to-kick-start-the-next-schedule-of-super-30-in-rajasthan-28543.html|website=Filmfare|title= Hrithik Roshan to kick-start the next schedule of Super 30 soon|date=29 May 2018|access-date=26 May 2019}}</ref> A set was erected in Mumbai at the cost of {{INR}}10 crore to recreate Patna city of Bihar to facilitate shooting.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/photo-features/most-talked-about-biopics-you-just-cannot-miss/Hrithik-Roshans-Super-30-team-to-spend-Rs-10-crore-to-recreate-Bihar-in-Mumbai/photostory/63015233.cms|title=Hrithik Roshan\u2019s \u2018Super 30\u2019 team to spend Rs 10 crore to recreate Bihar in Mumbai?|website=Times of India |date=23 February  2018|access-date=25 May 2019}}</ref> In second schedule of [[Varanasi]] shooting, the film was shot at [[Banaras Hindu University]] in the end of June 2018. This was the first Hindi film that the university allowed to be shot at its campus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/photo-features/movies-to-look-forward-to/hrithik-roshan-starrer-super-30-team-shoots-at-banaras-hindu-university/photostory/64841479.cms|title=Hrithik Roshan Starrer 'Super 30' team shoots at Banaras Hindu University|website=Times of India |date=3 July 2019|access-date=25 May 2019}}</ref> Filming was completed in September 2018.<ref name=\":p3\">{{cite news|url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/its-a-wrap-for-hrithik-roshan-super-30-celebrities-attend-bash-1869429.html|title=It's A Wrap for Hrithik Roshan's Super 30; Celebrities Attend Bash|publisher=CNN-News 18|date=6 September 2018|accessdate=26 May 2019}}</ref> Television actor [[Nandish Sandhu]] made his film debut in the film; he played Roshan's younger brother.\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Super 30\n| type       = soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Ajay\u2212Atul]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 9 July 2019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiosaavn.com/album/super-30/o7sj57DOh98_|title= Super 30 - Original Motion Picture Soundtrack |publisher=Jio Saavn}}</ref>\n| recorded   = 2018-2019\n| venue      = \n| studio     = \n| genre      = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 20:19\n| language   = Hindi\n| label      = [[Zee Music Company]]\n| producer   = [[Ajay\u2212Atul]]\n| prev_title = [[Zero (2018 film)|Zero]]\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = [[Jhund (film)|Jhund]]\n| next_year  = 2019\n| misc       = {{External media\n | audio1     = {{YouTube|Lf2qqLCMHis|Official Audio Jukebox}}\n}}}}\n\n[[Ajay Atul]] composed the music for the film and lyrics are written by [[Amitabh Bhattacharya]]. Vipin Nair of ''[[The Hindu]]'' gave the soundtrack 3.5/5, calling it a \"pretty engaging soundtrack \".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/breezy-blast-from-the-past/article28391666.ece|title='Super 30' music review: Breezy blast from the past|last=Nair|first=Vipin|date=2019-07-11|work=The Hindu|access-date=2019-07-17|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.musicaloud.com/2019/07/11/super-30-music-review-bollywood-soundtrack/|title=Super 30 \u2013 Music Review (Bollywood Soundtrack)|date=2019-07-11|website=Music Aloud|access-date=2019-07-17}}</ref> ''[[The Times of India]]'' based Debarati Sen, in her review, said the composers \"do not fail to impress\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/music/music-reviews/music-review-super-30/articleshow/70078286.cms|title=Music review: Super 30 - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-07-17}}</ref>\n\n{{Tracklist\n| headline=Track listing\n| total_length=20:19\n| all_writing=\n| extra_column=Singer(s)\n| title1= Jugraafiya\n| extra1= [[Udit Narayan]] & [[Shreya Ghoshal]]\n| length1= 4:34\n| title2= Paisa\n| extra2= [[Vishal Dadlani]]\n| length2= 3:52\n| title3= Basanti No Dance\n| extra3= Prem Areni, Janardan Dhatrak, [[Divya Kumar (singer)|Divya Kumar]] & Chaitally Parmar\n| length3= 5:04\n| title4= Question Mark\n| extra4= [[Hrithik Roshan]]\n| length4= 2:49\n| title5=Niyam Ho\n| extra5= Arohi Mhatre, Aditi Prabhudesai, Pragati Joshi, Maithili Panse, Sonal Naik, Rucha Soman, Deepti Rege, Deepanshi Nagar, Ann Fernandes, Dr. Pallavi Shyam Sundar, Shivika Rajesh, Riddhi Sampat, Kinjal Shah, Umesh Joshi, Vijay Dhuri, Mandar Pilvalkar, Vivek Naik, Rahul Chitnis, Saurabh Wakhare, Janardan Dhatrak, Gaurav Medatwal, Chaitanya Shinde, Abhishek Jhawar, Nimish Shah, Yash Kapoor & Mayukh Pareek\n| length5=3:00\n}}\n{{clear}}\n\n==Marketing and release==\nThe first look posters of Hrithik Roshan from ''Super 30'' were unveiled on 5 September 2018 to coincide with the [[List of Teachers' Days#Dates by country|Teacher's Day in India]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/hrithik-roshan-super-30-posters-teachers-day-5340410/|title=Hrithik Roshan unveils posters of Super 30 on Teacher\u2019s Day|website=Indian Express|access-date=25 May 2019|date=5 September 2018}}</ref> Second poster with new release date was revealed on 12 January 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.republicworld2rld.com/entertainment-news/bollywood-news/hrithik-roshans-super-30-gets-a-new-release-date-details-here|title=Bollywood actor Hrithik Roshan's much-anticipated venture 'Super 30' gets a new release date|website=Republic World|access-date=25 May 2019|date=12 January 2019}}</ref> Another look of Hrithik Roshan from the film unveiled in new poster on 2 June.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=taran_adarsh| author=Taran Adarsh|date=2 June 2019|number=1135074262782316544?s=19|title=Hrithik Roshan... First look poster of #Super30... 12 July 2019 release. https://t.co/rFVBjh8efV}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-super-30-hrithik-roshan-releases-new-poster-with-new-release-date-vikas-bahl-back-as-director-2756379|title='Super 30': Hrithik Roshan releases new poster with new release date; Vikas Bahl back as director|work=DNS|access-date=2019-06-02|language=en-US}}</ref> The next day another poster with Roshan soaking in the rain of success with motto \"Misaal Bano, Haqdaar Bano\" ({{transl|en|Be an example, be qualified}}) was released.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/hrithik-roshan-inspires-youngsters-with-the-new-poster-of-super-30-misaal-bano-haqdaar-bano-1541374-2019-06-03|title=Hrithik Roshan inspires youngsters with new poster of Super 30: Misaal Bano, Haqdaar Bano|website=India Today|access-date=4 June 2019|date=3 June 2019}}</ref> one day later on 4 June official trailer of the film was released by Reliance Entertainment. It garnered 44.99 million views since its release on YouTube.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=QpvEWVVnICE|title=Super 30 Official Trailer {{!}} Hrithik Roshan {{!}} Vikas Bahl {{!}} July 12 |publisher=Reliance Entertainment|website=YouTube|date=4 June 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe film's producer reported that Hrithik Roshan will be accompanied by Anand Kumar for the promotion of ''Super 30''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/super-30-promotions-will-see-hrithik-roshan-and-anand-kumar-together-details-here-1500285-2019-04-12|title=Super 30 promotions will see Hrithik Roshan and Anand Kumar together|work=India Today|access-date=2019-04-13}}</ref>\n\nThe film was theatrically released in India on 12 July 2019, as the release date was advanced by fourteen days.<ref name=\"rd\">{{cite web|url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/hrithik-roshans-super-30-finally-gets-a-release-date-34035.html|website=Filmfare|title= Hrithik Roshan\u2019s Super 30 finally gets a release date|date=23 May 2019|access-date=24 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe film has been certified with a runtime of 155 mins by [[British Board of Film Classification]] and was released on 12 July 2019.<ref name=\"bbfc\"/>\n\n== Reception ==\n=== Critical response ===\nThe film received mixed reviews from critics.<ref name=\":cr2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/super-30-movie-review-rating-hrithik-roshans-film-impresses-critics-early-shows-801400|title=Super 30 movie review and rating: Critics' verdict on Hrithik Roshan's film|website=IB Times|date=11 July 2019|accessdate=13 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nSreeparna Sengupta of ''[[The Times of India]]'' gave the film three and a half stars out of five, and praised [[Hrithik Roshan]], [[Pankaj Tripathi]], [[Aditya Srivastava]] and cinematography of Anay Goswami. She felt that ''Super 30'' conveyed the message that though education is the privilege of people with good economic background, if given the level field others too can shine equally. Concluding, she wrote \"While the narrative does have its flaws, ''Super 30'' is a human drama and the story of a teacher who triumphs over the many challenges that life throws at him, to set an example for the world to see. Just for that it\u2019s worth a watch.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-reviews/super-30/movie-review/70165930.cms|title=Super 30 Movie Review|work=The Times of India|first=Sreeparna|last=Sengupta|date=11 July 2019|access-date=12 July 2019}}</ref> Writing for the ''[[NDTV]]'' [[Saibal Chatterjee]], rated it with two stars out of five and felt that erratic screenplay of ''Super 30'' had 'skimmed the surface of a massive mound of tangled issues', and that Hrithik Roshan was miscast as [[Anand Kumar]]. He opined that the major problem with the film was telling a true story, which was not convincing. He concluded the review as, \"The idea to bronze up Hrithik Roshan so that he can impersonate Anand Kumar is anything but super: it is a formula that equals zero.\" <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/super-30-movie-review-bronzing-hrithik-roshan-up-to-play-anand-kumar-is-a-formula-that-equals-zero-2-2068243|title=Super 30 Movie Review: Bronzing Hrithik Roshan Up To Play Anand Kumar Is A Formula That Equals Zero|last=Chatterjee|first=Saibal|date=12 July 2019|website=NDTV|accessdate=12 July 2019}}</ref> Samrudhi Ghosh of ''[[India Today]]'' rated it with two and a half stars out of five, but praised the performances of [[Pankaj Tripathi]] and [[Aditya Srivastava]]. Ghosh felt the film was lengthy and had aroused the dramatics without need, saying \"Under the guidance of math wizard Anand Kumar, his Super 30 turned out to be miracles. Under the guidance of Vikas Bahl, Hrithik Roshan's Super 30 is far from one.\"<ref>{{cite news|first=Samrudhi |last=Ghosh |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/reviews/story/super-30-movie-review-hrithik-roshan-is-sincere-as-anand-kumar-vikas-bahl-s-story-not-quite-1567063-2019-07-11 |title=Super 30 Movie Review: Hrithik Roshan is sincere as Anand Kumar, Vikas Bahl's story not quite |date=11 July 2019 |work=India Today |accessdate=12 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nPriyanka Sinha Jha of [[CNN-News18]], disagreeing with Ghosh praises Roshan and ensemble of Pankaj Tripathi, Virendra Saxena, Nandish Sandhu and [[Aditya Srivastav]] for their performances. She feels that Roshan has given an admirable performance. Agreeing with Sengupta she opines that education is a means to a better life, but is a privilege in itself, and that is what the film questions and challenges. She rates the film with three stars out of five, and concludes,  \"After all, as the famous saying goes\u2014\u201cNot all superheroes wear capes.\u201d ''Super 30'' is the story of one such..\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/super-30-movie-review-hrithik-roshan-fills-colours-in-this-underdog-story-2226443.html|title=Super 30 Movie Review: Hrithik Roshan Fills Colours in this Underdog Story|last=Sinha Jha|first=Priyanka|date=12 July 2019|work=[[CNN-News18]]|access-date=12 July 2019}}</ref> Shubhra Gupta of ''[[The Indian Express]]'' gave two stars out of five and termed the film 'way less than super', she opined that if handled in right way, it would have been a 'rousing, goosebumps-inducing, cheer-athon.' She summarised by stating, \"Yes, the real-life story is inspiring. But the telling of it is a drag. The film has its moments, which belong mostly to its young people: the kids are all right.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/super-30-movie-review-rating-hrithik-roshan-5826356/ |title=Super 30 movie review: The Hrithik Roshan starrer is way less than super|first=Shubhra |last=Gupta |date=12 July 2019 |work=[[The Indian Express]] |accessdate=12 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Box office===\n''Super 30'' collected {{INR}}11.83 crore  from India, and {{INR}}6.18 crore from overseas on the opening day.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=taran_adarsh|author=Taran Adarsh|date=13 July 2019|number=1149990439795097601?s=19|title=#Super30 Overseas Day 1: $902k [\u20b9 6.18 cr]... Key markets... North America: $ 226k Middle East:Thu $ 192k, Fri $ 331k UK: $ 35k ANZ and Fiji: $ 47k Rest of the world: $ 71k}}</ref> Next day (Saturday) showing upward trend the film colllected {{INR}}18.19 crore from India, and {{INR}}5.46 crore from overseas.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=taran_adarsh|author=Taran Adarsh|date=14 July 2019|number=1150392822182240257?s=19|title=#Super30 - Overseas... Day 1: $ 902k Day 2: $ 795k Total: $ 1.697 million [\u20b9 11.64 cr]}}</ref> The film grossed {{INR}}75.08 crore in the opening weekend, and {{INR}}112.65 crore in the opening week worldwide.\n\n{{As of|2019|08|14|}}, with gross of {{INR}}172.84 crore from India and {{INR}}36.09 crore from overseas, the film has grossed {{INR}}208.93 crore worldwide.<ref name=\"boxtop\"/> The film entered the [[100 Crore Club|100 crore club]] on 21 July 2019.\n\n==Home media==\nThe film became available as [[Video on demand|VOD]] on [[Hotstar]] on 10 September 2019.<ref>{{cite web|title=Super 30|url=https://www.hotstar.com/1260009172|date=September 2019|accessdate=10 September 2019|website=Hotstar}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|tt7485048|Super 30}}\n* {{Facebook|Super30film}}\n* {{Twitter|Super30film}}\n* {{Instagram|Super30film}}\n*[http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/super-30/ Super 30] at [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/super_30_2019}}\n\n{{Sajid Nadiadwala}}\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Indian biographical films]]\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:Films based on real people]]\n[[Category:2010s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Reliance Entertainment films]]\n[[Category:Films featuring an item number]]\n[[Category:Films set in Patna]]\n[[Category:Biographical films about educators]]\n[[Category:Films about education]]\n[[Category:2010s biographical films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 Indian Hindi-language biographical film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Super 30\n| image          = Super 30 The Film.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = {{ubl|[[Vikas Bahl]]}}\n| producer       = {{ubl|[[Phantom Films]]|[[Nadiadwala Grandson Entertainment]]|[[Reliance Entertainment]]}}\n| starring       = {{ubl|[[Hrithik Roshan]]|[[Mrunal Thakur]]|[[Virendra Saxena]]|[[Pankaj Tripathi]]|[[Aditya Srivastava]]|[[Amit Sadh]]}}\n| writer         = Sanjeev Dutta\n| based on  = [[Anand Kumar]]\n| music          = [[Ajay\u2212Atul]]\n| cinematography = [[Anay Goswamy]]\n| editing        = [[A. Sreekar Prasad]]\n| studio         = {{ubl|[[Phantom Films]]|[[Nadiadwala Grandson Entertainment]]|[[Reliance Entertainment]]|HRX Films}}\n| distributor    = [[Reliance Entertainment]]<br>[[PVR Pictures]]\n| country        = India\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|07|12|df=y|}}\n| runtime        = 155 minutes<ref name=\"bbfc\">{{Citation |url=https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/super-30-2019 |title=Super 30 |publisher=[[British Board of Film Classification]] |access-date=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n| language       = Hindi\n| budget         = {{INR|link=yes}}60 [[crore]]<ref name=\"budget\">{{cite web |title=Super 30: Hrithik Roshan Starrer Is Made At THIS Budget & Not 110 Or 120 Crores? |url=https://www.koimoi.com/box-office/super-30-hrithik-roshan-starrer-is-made-at-this-budget-not-110-or-120-crores/ |website=www.koimoi.com |publisher=Koimoi |accessdate=13 August 2019}}</ref>\n| gross          =  {{INR}}208.93 crore<ref name=\"boxtop\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/super-30/box-office/|title=Super 30 Box Office|website=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|accessdate=14 August 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"boxtg\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/box-office-collections/worldwide/2019/|title=Bollywood Top Grossers Worldwide Bollywood Hungama|access-date=15 August 2019|website=[[Bollywood Hungama]]}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Super 30''''' is a 2019 Indian [[Hindi]]-language [[biographical film|biographical]] [[drama film]] directed by [[Vikas Bahl]] and co-produced by [[Sajid Nadiadwala]] on a budget of {{INRConvert|60|c}}, narrating the life of mathematician [[Anand Kumar]] and his  [[Super 30|educational program of the same name]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/super-30-first-look-anand-kumar-says-hrithik-roshans-resemblance-to-him-is-uncanny-4340299.html|title=Super 30 first look: Anand Kumar says Hrithik Roshan's resemblance to him is 'uncanny'|publisher=Firstpost|date=7 February 2018|accessdate=9 February 2018}}</ref> Co-distributed by [[Reliance Entertainment]], the film stars [[Hrithik Roshan]] as Anand, with [[Mrunal Thakur]], [[Virendra Saxena]], [[Pankaj Tripathi]], [[Aditya Srivastava]], Nandish Singh and [[Amit Sadh]] in supporting roles.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/photo-features/most-talked-about-biopics-you-just-cannot-miss/super-30-first-look-hrithik-roshan-looks-convincing-as-he-steps-into-math-genius-anand-kumars-shoes/photostory/62801512.cms|title=Most talked about biopics you just cannot miss|work=The Times of India|date=8 February 2018|accessdate=9 February 2018}}</ref> \n\n''Super 30'' was Phantom Film's last production.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/anurag-kashyap-partners-dissolve-of-phantom-films-of-queen-udta-punjab-fame-super-30-to-be-banners-last-1900411.html|title=Phantom Films Dissolved, Vikas Bahl's Super 30 will be Banner's Last Film|work=News18|access-date=2018-11-19}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/hrithik-roshans-super-30-actress-mrunal-thakur-spotted-on-set-see-pics-1810560|title=Hrithik Roshan's Super 30: Actress Mrunal Thakur Spotted On Set. See Pics|last=Shiksha|first=Shruti|publisher=NDTV|date=|accessdate=9 February 2018}}</ref> [[Principal photography]] began in February 2018 and the film was extensively shot in Ramnagar Fort and [[Sambhar Lake Town]] which was shown as [[Kota, Rajasthan]].<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite news|url=http://ahmedabadmirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/discovery-of-india/articleshow/63356801.cms|title=From Meghna Gulzar to Vikas Bahl, filmmakers explore the untapped interiors of India|last=Iyer|first=Sanyukta|work=Mumbai Mirror|date=19 March 2018|accessdate=25 March 2018}}</ref> ''Super 30'' was theatrically released in India on 12 July 2019 and received positive to mixed reviews, but with some praise for the storyline and Roshan's performance.<ref name=\":cr2\"/><ref name=\"boxtg\"/> With worldwide earnings of {{INRConvert|208.93|c}}, the film emerged as one of the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing Indian films]]. Based on domestic net collection, the film stands among top 40 in the list of [[List of highest domestic net collection of Hindi films|Hindi films with highest India net collection]] with a lifetime [[net income|net]] gross of {{INRConvert|146.95|c}} in India.\n\n==Plot==\n\n[[Anand Kumar]] is a lower-class student who has a passion in studies and is good at it. At a local competition felicitation, the local minister, Shriram Singh, proud of him, promises for help whenever needed.\n\nAnand frequently goes to Banaras Hindu University's library to solve a foreign Math journal. One day, the manager finally catches him, and says that he has no right to read there. One staff member suggests him to get his article published in this journal and earn a free lifetime subscription to it. Anand goes to the post-office, where his father Rajendra works as the head, and posts a letter regarding the solution to a difficult Math problem that no one has been able to solve yet. He then gets featured in the journal for solving the problem, and gets a letter from Professor Richard of the [[University of Cambridge]] to join a program there. But Anand needs money to travel. He and Rajendra go to Shriram but he denies any promise. They both further try to collect money but remain helpless, and get depressed. One day, Rajendra dies of a heart attack. Anand refuses to go to Cambridge due to his father's death and financial condition.\n\nHe then sells [[Papadum|papads]] in the city. One day, he meets Lallan Singh, an assistant of the local minister. Lallan takes Anand as a teacher in his coaching centre, Excellence Coaching Centre. There, Anand sees the plight of a boy who had to leave due to poverty. He thinks that these poor kids also have a right to study. Hence, he leaves Excellence and starts a separate tuition for poor kids, in which he enrolls 30 kids at a time. He teaches them to learn everything practically and have the concepts cleared in an easy and fun way. All this enrages Lallan, whose centre is facing criticism for not retaining Anand.\n\nIn course of the tuition, Anand gets immense help from his brother Pranav and his mother. Lallan and Shriram plan to have Anand killed so that his kids won't be entering [[Indian Institutes of Technology|IIT]]. Anand is hurt brutally by two of Lallan's henchmen, and is hospitalised, on the verge of death. He tells his students to then use their knowledge to defeat the goons sent by Shriram, while he is being treated. The students, in unity, use their knowledge and defeat the goons and Anand is treated successfully. The students take the IIT exam and all 30 students pass successfully.\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Hrithik Roshan]] as [[Anand Kumar]], a [[Mathematician|mathematician]] who opens a program named Super 30 where he teaches 30 students for [[Indian Institutes of Technology|IIT]] in free cost.\n* [[Mrunal Thakur]] as Supriya, Anand's love interest.\n* [[Virendra Saxena]] as Rajendra Kumar,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/on-sets-hrithik-roshan-loses-weight-for-his-role-in-super-30/19433190|title=On sets: Hrithik Roshan loses weight for his role in Super 30|date=2018-05-18|work=mid-day|access-date=2018-08-09|language=en}}</ref> Anand's father who dies after suffering from a heart attack.\n* [[Nandish Sandhu|Nandish Singh]] as Pranav Kumar,<ref>{{cite web|title=Meet Nandish Singh, who plays Hrithik Roshan's brother in 'Super 30'|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-meet-nandish-singh-who-plays-hrithik-roshan-s-brother-in-super-30-2589947|website=dnaindia.com|date=2 March 2018|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref> Anand's brother.\n* [[Aditya Shrivastava]] as Lallan Singh, Shri Ram's assistant.\n* [[Sadhana Singh]] as Jayanti Kumar, Anand's mother.\n* [[Pankaj Tripathi]] as Shri Ram Singh,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-pankaj-tripathi-to-play-hrithik-roshan-aka-anand-kumar-s-arch-rival-in-super-30-2625091|title=Pankaj Tripathi to play Hrithik Roshan aka Anand Kumar's arch-rival in Super 30|date=2018-06-13|work=dna|access-date=2018-08-09|language=en-US}}</ref> a local minister.\n*[[Vijay Varma]] as Fugga Kumar\n* [[Amit Sadh]] as Raghunath<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/amit-sadh-is-super-30s-sutradhar/articleshow/64753466.cms|title=Amit Sadh is the narrator for Hrithik Roshan-starrer Super 30|work=Mumbai Mirror|access-date=2018-08-09}}</ref>\n*Sharat Sonu as Haadim Malik, Shriram's secretary.\n*[[Manav Gohil]] as Purushottam\n*Aayush Kumar Shukla as Vinod\n*[[Rahul Raj]] as Kishore\n*Deepali Gautam as Kusum\n*[[Ali Haji (actor)|Ali Haji]] as Prithvi\n*[[Rajesh Sharma (actor)|Rajesh Sharma]] as Bachchi\n*[[Karishma Sharma]] in [[item number]] \"Paisa\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.desimartini.com/news/martini-shots/breakdowns/super-30s-paisa-song-hrithik-roshan-shows-the-power-money-can-give-article112078.htm|title=Super 30\u2019s Paisa Song: Hrithik Roshan Shows The Power Money Can Give!|date=21 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/super-30-new-song-paisa-hrithik-roshan-as-anand-kumar-shows-importance-of-money-1553307-2019-06-21|title=Super 30 new song Paisa: Hrithik Roshan as Anand Kumar shows importance of money|date=22 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n[[Mrunal Thakur]] was cast opposite Hrithik Roshan in the film. The film was shot at [[Ramnagar Fort]]; part of the fort was converted to look like the Super 30 institute.<ref name=\":p1\">{{cite news|url=http://www.news18.com/news/movies/super-30-kumkum-bhagya-star-mrunal-thakur-to-play-hrithik-roshan-love-interest-in-the-film-1655299.html|title=Super 30: Kumkum Bhagya Star Mrunal Thakur To Play Hrithik Roshan's Love Interest In The Film?|publisher=CNN-News 18|date=9 February 2018|accessdate=9 February 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\"/> The film was also shot for ten days in [[Sambhar Lake Town]] which was shown as [[Kota, Rajasthan]] and Jaipur.<ref name=\"auto\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/hrithik-roshan-to-kick-start-the-next-schedule-of-super-30-in-rajasthan-28543.html|website=Filmfare|title= Hrithik Roshan to kick-start the next schedule of Super 30 soon|date=29 May 2018|access-date=26 May 2019}}</ref> A set was erected in Mumbai at the cost of {{INR}}10 crore to recreate Patna city of Bihar to facilitate shooting.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/photo-features/most-talked-about-biopics-you-just-cannot-miss/Hrithik-Roshans-Super-30-team-to-spend-Rs-10-crore-to-recreate-Bihar-in-Mumbai/photostory/63015233.cms|title=Hrithik Roshan\u2019s \u2018Super 30\u2019 team to spend Rs 10 crore to recreate Bihar in Mumbai?|website=Times of India |date=23 February  2018|access-date=25 May 2019}}</ref> In second schedule of [[Varanasi]] shooting, the film was shot at [[Banaras Hindu University]] in the end of June 2018. This was the first Hindi film that the university allowed to be shot at its campus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/photo-features/movies-to-look-forward-to/hrithik-roshan-starrer-super-30-team-shoots-at-banaras-hindu-university/photostory/64841479.cms|title=Hrithik Roshan Starrer 'Super 30' team shoots at Banaras Hindu University|website=Times of India |date=3 July 2019|access-date=25 May 2019}}</ref> Filming was completed in September 2018.<ref name=\":p3\">{{cite news|url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/its-a-wrap-for-hrithik-roshan-super-30-celebrities-attend-bash-1869429.html|title=It's A Wrap for Hrithik Roshan's Super 30; Celebrities Attend Bash|publisher=CNN-News 18|date=6 September 2018|accessdate=26 May 2019}}</ref> Television actor [[Nandish Sandhu]] made his film debut in the film; he played Roshan's younger brother.\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Super 30\n| type       = soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Ajay\u2212Atul]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 9 July 2019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiosaavn.com/album/super-30/o7sj57DOh98_|title= Super 30 - Original Motion Picture Soundtrack |publisher=Jio Saavn}}</ref>\n| recorded   = 2018-2019\n| venue      = \n| studio     = \n| genre      = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 20:19\n| language   = Hindi\n| label      = [[Zee Music Company]]\n| producer   = [[Ajay\u2212Atul]]\n| prev_title = [[Zero (2018 film)|Zero]]\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = [[Jhund (film)|Jhund]]\n| next_year  = 2019\n| misc       = {{External media\n | audio1     = {{YouTube|Lf2qqLCMHis|Official Audio Jukebox}}\n}}}}\n\n[[Ajay Atul]] composed the music for the film and lyrics are written by [[Amitabh Bhattacharya]]. Vipin Nair of ''[[The Hindu]]'' gave the soundtrack 3.5/5, calling it a \"pretty engaging soundtrack \".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/breezy-blast-from-the-past/article28391666.ece|title='Super 30' music review: Breezy blast from the past|last=Nair|first=Vipin|date=2019-07-11|work=The Hindu|access-date=2019-07-17|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.musicaloud.com/2019/07/11/super-30-music-review-bollywood-soundtrack/|title=Super 30 \u2013 Music Review (Bollywood Soundtrack)|date=2019-07-11|website=Music Aloud|access-date=2019-07-17}}</ref> ''[[The Times of India]]'' based Debarati Sen, in her review, said the composers \"do not fail to impress\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/music/music-reviews/music-review-super-30/articleshow/70078286.cms|title=Music review: Super 30 - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-07-17}}</ref>\n\n{{Tracklist\n| headline=Track listing\n| total_length=20:19\n| all_writing=\n| extra_column=Singer(s)\n| title1= Jugraafiya\n| extra1= [[Udit Narayan]] & [[Shreya Ghoshal]]\n| length1= 4:34\n| title2= Paisa\n| extra2= [[Vishal Dadlani]]\n| length2= 3:52\n| title3= Basanti No Dance\n| extra3= Prem Areni, Janardan Dhatrak, [[Divya Kumar (singer)|Divya Kumar]] & Chaitally Parmar\n| length3= 5:04\n| title4= Question Mark\n| extra4= [[Hrithik Roshan]]\n| length4= 2:49\n| title5=Niyam Ho\n| extra5= Arohi Mhatre, Aditi Prabhudesai, Pragati Joshi, Maithili Panse, Sonal Naik, Rucha Soman, Deepti Rege, Deepanshi Nagar, Ann Fernandes, Dr. Pallavi Shyam Sundar, Shivika Rajesh, Riddhi Sampat, Kinjal Shah, Umesh Joshi, Vijay Dhuri, Mandar Pilvalkar, Vivek Naik, Rahul Chitnis, Saurabh Wakhare, Janardan Dhatrak, Gaurav Medatwal, Chaitanya Shinde, Abhishek Jhawar, Nimish Shah, Yash Kapoor & Mayukh Pareek\n| length5=3:00\n}}\n{{clear}}\n\n==Marketing and release==\nThe first look posters of Hrithik Roshan from ''Super 30'' were unveiled on 5 September 2018 to coincide with the [[List of Teachers' Days#Dates by country|Teacher's Day in India]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/hrithik-roshan-super-30-posters-teachers-day-5340410/|title=Hrithik Roshan unveils posters of Super 30 on Teacher\u2019s Day|website=Indian Express|access-date=25 May 2019|date=5 September 2018}}</ref> Second poster with new release date was revealed on 12 January 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.republicworld2rld.com/entertainment-news/bollywood-news/hrithik-roshans-super-30-gets-a-new-release-date-details-here|title=Bollywood actor Hrithik Roshan's much-anticipated venture 'Super 30' gets a new release date|website=Republic World|access-date=25 May 2019|date=12 January 2019}}</ref> Another look of Hrithik Roshan from the film unveiled in new poster on 2 June.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=taran_adarsh| author=Taran Adarsh|date=2 June 2019|number=1135074262782316544?s=19|title=Hrithik Roshan... First look poster of #Super30... 12 July 2019 release. https://t.co/rFVBjh8efV}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-super-30-hrithik-roshan-releases-new-poster-with-new-release-date-vikas-bahl-back-as-director-2756379|title='Super 30': Hrithik Roshan releases new poster with new release date; Vikas Bahl back as director|work=DNS|access-date=2019-06-02|language=en-US}}</ref> The next day another poster with Roshan soaking in the rain of success with motto \"Misaal Bano, Haqdaar Bano\" ({{transl|en|Be an example, be qualified}}) was released.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/hrithik-roshan-inspires-youngsters-with-the-new-poster-of-super-30-misaal-bano-haqdaar-bano-1541374-2019-06-03|title=Hrithik Roshan inspires youngsters with new poster of Super 30: Misaal Bano, Haqdaar Bano|website=India Today|access-date=4 June 2019|date=3 June 2019}}</ref> one day later on 4 June official trailer of the film was released by Reliance Entertainment. It garnered 44.99 million views since its release on YouTube.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=QpvEWVVnICE|title=Super 30 Official Trailer {{!}} Hrithik Roshan {{!}} Vikas Bahl {{!}} July 12 |publisher=Reliance Entertainment|website=YouTube|date=4 June 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe film's producer reported that Hrithik Roshan will be accompanied by Anand Kumar for the promotion of ''Super 30''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/super-30-promotions-will-see-hrithik-roshan-and-anand-kumar-together-details-here-1500285-2019-04-12|title=Super 30 promotions will see Hrithik Roshan and Anand Kumar together|work=India Today|access-date=2019-04-13}}</ref>\n\nThe film was theatrically released in India on 12 July 2019, as the release date was advanced by fourteen days.<ref name=\"rd\">{{cite web|url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/hrithik-roshans-super-30-finally-gets-a-release-date-34035.html|website=Filmfare|title= Hrithik Roshan\u2019s Super 30 finally gets a release date|date=23 May 2019|access-date=24 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe film has been certified with a runtime of 155 mins by [[British Board of Film Classification]] and was released on 12 July 2019.<ref name=\"bbfc\"/>\n\n== Reception ==\n=== Critical response ===\nThe film received mixed reviews from critics.<ref name=\":cr2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/super-30-movie-review-rating-hrithik-roshans-film-impresses-critics-early-shows-801400|title=Super 30 movie review and rating: Critics' verdict on Hrithik Roshan's film|website=IB Times|date=11 July 2019|accessdate=13 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nSreeparna Sengupta of ''[[The Times of India]]'' gave the film three and a half stars out of five, and praised [[Hrithik Roshan]], [[Pankaj Tripathi]], [[Aditya Srivastava]] and cinematography of Anay Goswami. She felt that ''Super 30'' conveyed the message that though education is the privilege of people with good economic background, if given the level field others too can shine equally. Concluding, she wrote \"While the narrative does have its flaws, ''Super 30'' is a human drama and the story of a teacher who triumphs over the many challenges that life throws at him, to set an example for the world to see. Just for that it\u2019s worth a watch.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-reviews/super-30/movie-review/70165930.cms|title=Super 30 Movie Review|work=The Times of India|first=Sreeparna|last=Sengupta|date=11 July 2019|access-date=12 July 2019}}</ref> Writing for the ''[[NDTV]]'' [[Saibal Chatterjee]], rated it with two stars out of five and felt that erratic screenplay of ''Super 30'' had 'skimmed the surface of a massive mound of tangled issues', and that Hrithik Roshan was miscast as [[Anand Kumar]]. He opined that the major problem with the film was telling a true story, which was not convincing. He concluded the review as, \"The idea to bronze up Hrithik Roshan so that he can impersonate Anand Kumar is anything but super: it is a formula that equals zero.\" <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/super-30-movie-review-bronzing-hrithik-roshan-up-to-play-anand-kumar-is-a-formula-that-equals-zero-2-2068243|title=Super 30 Movie Review: Bronzing Hrithik Roshan Up To Play Anand Kumar Is A Formula That Equals Zero|last=Chatterjee|first=Saibal|date=12 July 2019|website=NDTV|accessdate=12 July 2019}}</ref> Samrudhi Ghosh of ''[[India Today]]'' rated it with two and a half stars out of five, but praised the performances of [[Pankaj Tripathi]] and [[Aditya Srivastava]]. Ghosh felt the film was lengthy and had aroused the dramatics without need, saying \"Under the guidance of math wizard Anand Kumar, his Super 30 turned out to be miracles. Under the guidance of Vikas Bahl, Hrithik Roshan's Super 30 is far from one.\"<ref>{{cite news|first=Samrudhi |last=Ghosh |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/reviews/story/super-30-movie-review-hrithik-roshan-is-sincere-as-anand-kumar-vikas-bahl-s-story-not-quite-1567063-2019-07-11 |title=Super 30 Movie Review: Hrithik Roshan is sincere as Anand Kumar, Vikas Bahl's story not quite |date=11 July 2019 |work=India Today |accessdate=12 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nPriyanka Sinha Jha of [[CNN-News18]], disagreeing with Ghosh praises Roshan and ensemble of Pankaj Tripathi, Virendra Saxena, Nandish Sandhu and [[Aditya Srivastav]] for their performances. She feels that Roshan has given an admirable performance. Agreeing with Sengupta she opines that education is a means to a better life, but is a privilege in itself, and that is what the film questions and challenges. She rates the film with three stars out of five, and concludes,  \"After all, as the famous saying goes\u2014\u201cNot all superheroes wear capes.\u201d ''Super 30'' is the story of one such..\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/super-30-movie-review-hrithik-roshan-fills-colours-in-this-underdog-story-2226443.html|title=Super 30 Movie Review: Hrithik Roshan Fills Colours in this Underdog Story|last=Sinha Jha|first=Priyanka|date=12 July 2019|work=[[CNN-News18]]|access-date=12 July 2019}}</ref> Shubhra Gupta of ''[[The Indian Express]]'' gave two stars out of five and termed the film 'way less than super', she opined that if handled in right way, it would have been a 'rousing, goosebumps-inducing, cheer-athon.' She summarised by stating, \"Yes, the real-life story is inspiring. But the telling of it is a drag. The film has its moments, which belong mostly to its young people: the kids are all right.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/super-30-movie-review-rating-hrithik-roshan-5826356/ |title=Super 30 movie review: The Hrithik Roshan starrer is way less than super|first=Shubhra |last=Gupta |date=12 July 2019 |work=[[The Indian Express]] |accessdate=12 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Box office===\n''Super 30'' collected {{INR}}11.83 crore  from India, and {{INR}}6.18 crore from overseas on the opening day.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=taran_adarsh|author=Taran Adarsh|date=13 July 2019|number=1149990439795097601?s=19|title=#Super30 Overseas Day 1: $902k [\u20b9 6.18 cr]... Key markets... North America: $ 226k Middle East:Thu $ 192k, Fri $ 331k UK: $ 35k ANZ and Fiji: $ 47k Rest of the world: $ 71k}}</ref> Next day (Saturday) showing upward trend the film colllected {{INR}}18.19 crore from India, and {{INR}}5.46 crore from overseas.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=taran_adarsh|author=Taran Adarsh|date=14 July 2019|number=1150392822182240257?s=19|title=#Super30 - Overseas... Day 1: $ 902k Day 2: $ 795k Total: $ 1.697 million [\u20b9 11.64 cr]}}</ref> The film grossed {{INR}}75.08 crore in the opening weekend, and {{INR}}112.65 crore in the opening week worldwide.\n\n{{As of|2019|08|14|}}, with gross of {{INR}}172.84 crore from India and {{INR}}36.09 crore from overseas, the film has grossed {{INR}}208.93 crore worldwide.<ref name=\"boxtop\"/> The film entered the [[100 Crore Club|100 crore club]] on 21 July 2019.\n\n==Home media==\nThe film became available as [[Video on demand|VOD]] on [[Hotstar]] on 10 September 2019.<ref>{{cite web|title=Super 30|url=https://www.hotstar.com/1260009172|date=September 2019|accessdate=10 September 2019|website=Hotstar}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|tt7485048|Super 30}}\n* {{Facebook|Super30film}}\n* {{Twitter|Super30film}}\n* {{Instagram|Super30film}}\n*[http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/super-30/ Super 30] at [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/super_30_2019}}\n\n{{Sajid Nadiadwala}}\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Indian biographical films]]\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:Films based on real people]]\n[[Category:2010s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Reliance Entertainment films]]\n[[Category:Films featuring an item number]]\n[[Category:Films set in Patna]]\n[[Category:Biographical films about educators]]\n[[Category:Films about education]]\n[[Category:2010s biographical films]]\n", "name_user": "Rajmishra7648", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Super_30_(film)"}
{"title_page": "Doughboy (record producer)", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = Doughboy\n| image               = \n| caption             =\n| background          = non_performing_personnel\n| birth_name          = Bradley Brandon\n| alias               = {{hlist|Doughboy|Doughboy Beatz}}\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1989|09|01}}\n| birth_place         = United States\n| origin              = [[Columbus, Mississippi]], United States\n|genre           = {{flatlist|\n*[[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n*[[Trap music (hip hop)|trap]]\n*[[Rhythm and blues|R&B]]}}\n|occupation      = {{flatlist|\n*[[Record producer]]\n*[[songwriter]]\n}}\n| instrument          = [[FL Studio]]\n| years_active        = 2008\u2013present\n|label               = Boominati Worldwide, [[Republic Records|Republic]]\n|associated_acts = {{flatlist|\n*[[Metro Boomin]] \n*[[808 Mafia]]\n*[[Gunna (rapper)|Gunna]]\n*[[Shy Glizzy]]\n*[[Rich The Kid]]\n*[[Gucci Mane]]\n*[[Migos]]\n*[[21 Savage]]\n*[[Wheezy (record producer)|Wheezy]] \n*[[Juicy J]] \n*Trauma Tone\n}}}}\n'''Bradley Brandon''' (born September 1, 1989), professionally known as '''Doughboy Beatz''' or simply '''Doughboy''', is an American [[record producer]] from [[Columbus, Mississippi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://repertoire.bmi.com/Catalog.aspx?detail=writerid&page=1&fromrow=1&torow=25&keyid=1151209&subid=0|title=BMI Repertoire Bradley Brandon|publisher=BMI.com |date= |accessdate=December 26, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.doughboybeatz.com/bio |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181227064003/http://www.doughboybeatz.com/bio |url-status=dead |archive-date=December 27, 2018 |title=Doughboy Beatz - Bio |publisher=Doughboybeatz.com |date= |accessdate=December 26, 2018}}</ref> He is perhaps best known for producing \"[[Pedestrian (Gunna song)|Pedestrian]]\" by rapper [[Gunna (rapper)|Gunna]], as well as \"[[Lost It (Rich the Kid song)|Lost It]]\" by rapper [[Rich The Kid]] featuring [[Offset (rapper)|Offset]] and [[Quavo]] of [[Migos]] which was [[certified gold]] by the [[RIAA]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&se=rich+the+kid+lost+it#search_section|title=Gold & Platinum - RIAA|publisher=[[RIAA]]|accessdate=December 26, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"RTK\">{{cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2018/03/rich-the-kid-the-world-is-yours-album-production-credits/|title=Production Credits for Rich The Kid's 'The World Is Yours' Album|publisher=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]|accessdate=December 26, 2018}}</ref>\n\nDoughboy has [[hip hop production|produced]] several tracks for various artists such as [[Young Jeezy]], [[Gucci Mane]], [[Future (rapper)|Future]], [[Yo Gotti]], [[Juicy J]], [[21 Savage]], [[YoungBoy Never Broke Again|NBA Youngboy]], [[Lil Boosie]], [[Soulja Boy]], [[Shy Glizzy]], [[YFN Lucci]], [[Plies (rapper)|Plies]], [[Trina]], [[Crooked I]], [[B.G. (rapper)|B.G]], [[CyHi the Prynce]], among others.<ref name=\"DBG\">{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/artists/Doughboy-beatz|title=Doughboy Beatz on Genius|publisher=|accessdate=December 26, 2018}}</ref> He has earned a [[Grammy Nomination]] for his work on 21 Savage's ''[[I Am Greater than I Was|I Am > I Was]]'' for [[Grammy Award for Best Rap Album|Best Rap Album]] at the [[62nd Annual Grammy Awards]].\n\n==Early Life and Career==\nBrandon started making beats at the age of 15, for his younger brother on [[FL Studio]].<ref name=\"DBG\"/> He then went on to produce [[Hitz Committee]]/[[Jive Records]] signee, Trai'D's lead single \"Gutta Chick\" in 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://djbooth.net/songs/traid-gutta-chick |title=Trai'D - Gutta Chick |publisher=DJBbooth.net |date=|accessdate=December 26, 2018}}</ref> \"Gutta Chick\" peaked at number 72 on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] charts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/traid/chart-history/r-b-hip-hop-songs/song/540786 |title=Trai'D Chart History |publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=|accessdate=December 26, 2018}}</ref>  Doughboy has worked with many other major artists since then.\n\nThroughout the 2010s, Doughboy has followed up with production on many highly acclaimed projects that include [[Jeezy]]'s ''[[Trap or Die 2]]'', [[Shy Glizzy]]'s ''Law 3'', [[Rich The Kid]]'s ''[[The World Is Yours (Rich the Kid album)|The World Is Yours]]'', [[Gunna (rapper)|Gunna]]'s ''[[Drip Season 3]]'' and [[Gucci Mane]]'s ''[[East Atlanta Santa]]''.\n\nBrandon has also worked with other music producers that include [[Metro Boomin]], [[Wheezy (record producer)|Wheezy]], [[Drumma Boy]], [[Southside (record producer)|Southside]], [[Zaytoven]], [[Shawty Redd]], [[Sonny Digital]], [[Honorable C.N.O.T.E.]], [[DJ Paul]], [[Juicy J]] and more.\n\nIn September 2019, Doughboy signed with [[Metro Boomin]]'s Boominati Worldwide label.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MetroBoomin/status/1174728677206233090 |title=Metro Boomin on Twitter |publisher=[[Twitter]] |date=|accessdate=October 7, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/BoominatiWW/status/1174813473051688965 |title=Boominati Worldwide on Twitter |publisher=[[Twitter]] |date=|accessdate=October 7, 2019}}</ref>   Boominati Worldwide has a partnership with [[Republic Records]] and [[Universal Music Group]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/7849328/metro-boomin-boominati-worldwide-label-bryson-tiller-tour |title=Metro Boomin Launches Boominati Worldwide Label, Joins Bryson Tiller on Set It Off Tour |publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=|accessdate=October 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n=== Studio albums ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of studio albums, with selected details\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:12em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:19em;\" | Album details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''October 31st''<br/><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">