er)|Plies]] - [[Ain't No Mixtape Bih 3]]'''\n* 18. \"Best Life\" <small>(Produced with Trauma Tone)</small><ref>{{cite web|title= Plies - Best Life|url=https://genius.com/Plies-best-life-lyrics|website=Genius.com|accessdate=December 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\n'''Q Money - Neva Had Shit'''\n* 09. \"Whole Ticket\" (feat. [[YFN Lucci]])<small>(Produced with Trauma Tone)</small><ref>{{cite web|title= Q Money - Whole Ticket|url=https://genius.com/Q-money-whole-ticket-lyrics|website=Genius.com|accessdate=December 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Rich The Kid]] - [[The World Is Yours (Rich the Kid album)|The World Is Yours]]''' \n* 09. \"Lost It\" (feat. [[Offset (rapper)|Offset]] & [[Quavo]] of [[Migos]]) <small>(Produced with [[Metro Boomin]] & [[Wheezy (record producer)|Wheezy]])</small><ref name=\"RTK\"/>\n\n'''[[Shy Glizzy]] - Fully Loaded'''\n* 18. \"I Need Mo\"<ref>{{cite web|title= Shy Glizzy - I Need Mo|url=https://genius.com/Shy-glizzy-i-need-mo-lyrics|website=Genius.com|accessdate=December 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\n'''[[21 Savage]] - [[I Am Greater Than I Was|I Am > I Was]]'''\n* 02. \"Break Da Law\" <small>(Produced with [[Metro Boomin]] & [[Southside (record producer)|Southside]])</small><ref>{{cite web|title= 21 Savage - break da law|url=https://genius.com/21-savage-break-da-law-lyrics|website=Genius.com|accessdate=December 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===2019===\n\n'''[[Offset (rapper)|Offset]] - [[Father of 4]]'''\n* 09. \"Don't Lose Me\" <small>(Produced with [[Metro Boomin]])</small><ref>{{cite web|title= Offset - Don't Lose Me|url=https://genius.com/Offset-dont-lose-me-lyrics|website=Genius.com|accessdate=February 23, 2019}}</ref>\n* 09. \"On Fleek\" (feat. [[Quavo]]) <small>(Produced with [[Metro Boomin]] & [[Zaytoven]])</small><ref>{{cite web|title= Here Are the Full Production Credits for Offset's 'Father of 4'|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2019/02/here-are-the-full-production-credits-for-offsets-father-of-4|website=Complex.com|accessdate=February 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Gunna (rapper)|Gunna]]\n* 00. \"Mr. T\" <small>(Produced with [[Metro Boomin]])</small><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/doughboybeatz/status/1124152964292186113|title=Doughboy \"Prod. by Metro Boomin & Doughboy\"|publisher=[[Twitter]]|accessdate=May 3, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title= Gunna - Mr. T|url=https://genius.com/Gunna-mr-t-lyrics|website=Genius.com|accessdate=May 3, 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Future (rapper)|Future]]'''\n* 00. \"Perkies\" <small>(Produced with [[Metro Boomin]])</small><ref>{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/Future-perkies-lyrics|title=Future - Perkies Lyrics|publisher=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|accessdate=Aug 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''[[D-Block Europe]] - PTSD'''\n* 23. \"Back To Back\" <small>(Produced with [[808 Mafia|Tre Pounds of 808 Mafia]])</small><ref>{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/D-block-europe-back-to-back-lyrics|title=D-Block Europe - Back To Back Lyrics|publisher=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|accessdate=Nov 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Gucci Mane]] - [[Woptober II]]'''\n* 13. \"Break Bread\" <small>(Produced with [[Metro Boomin]])</small><ref>{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/Gucci-mane-break-bread-lyrics|title=Gucci Mane - Break Bread Lyrics|publisher=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|accessdate=Nov 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''BAD HOP - Lift Off'''\n* 02. \"Double Up\" <small>(Produced with [[Metro Boomin]])</small>\n\n'''[[Gucci Mane]] - East Atlanta Santa 3'''\n* 9. \u201cShe Miss Me\u201d (feat. [[Rich The Kid]]) <small>(Produced with [[Metro Boomin]] & [[Dre Moon]])</small><ref>{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/Gucci-mane-she-miss-me-lyrics|title=Gucci Mane - She Miss Me Lyrics|publisher=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|accessdate=Dec 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20190417193815/http://www.doughboybeatz.com/ Official Web site]\n* {{Allmusic|class=artist|id=mn0003627444|label=Doughboy}}\n* {{Discogs artist | artist=Doughboy+Beatz | name=Doughboy }}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Doughboy}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:African-American record producers]]\n[[Category:American hip hop record producers]]\n[[Category:Southern hip hop musicians]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Mississippi]]\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = Doughboy\n| image               = Doughboy Beatz Press Photo 2019.png\n| caption             =\n| background          = non_performing_personnel\n| birth_name          = Bradley Brandon\n| alias               = {{hlist|Doughboy|Doughboy Beatz}}\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1989|09|01}}\n| birth_place         = United States\n| origin              = [[Columbus, Mississippi]], United States\n|genre           = {{flatlist|\n*[[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n*[[Trap music (hip hop)|trap]]\n*[[Rhythm and blues|R&B]]}}\n|occupation      = {{flatlist|\n*[[Record producer]]\n*[[songwriter]]\n}}\n| instrument          = [[FL Studio]]\n| years_active        = 2008\u2013present\n|label               = Boominati Worldwide, [[Republic Records|Republic]]\n|associated_acts = {{flatlist|\n*[[Metro Boomin]] \n*[[808 Mafia]]\n*[[Gunna (rapper)|Gunna]]\n*[[Shy Glizzy]]\n*[[Rich The Kid]]\n*[[Gucci Mane]]\n*[[Migos]]\n*[[21 Savage]]\n*[[Wheezy (record producer)|Wheezy]] \n*[[Juicy J]] \n*Trauma Tone\n}}}}\n'''Bradley Brandon''' (born September 1, 1989), professionally known as '''Doughboy Beatz''' or simply '''Doughboy''', is an American [[record producer]] from [[Columbus, Mississippi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://repertoire.bmi.com/Catalog.aspx?detail=writerid&page=1&fromrow=1&torow=25&keyid=1151209&subid=0|title=BMI Repertoire Bradley Brandon|publisher=BMI.com |date= |accessdate=December 26, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.doughboybeatz.com/bio |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181227064003/http://www.doughboybeatz.com/bio |url-status=dead |archive-date=December 27, 2018 |title=Doughboy Beatz - Bio |publisher=Doughboybeatz.com |date= |accessdate=December 26, 2018}}</ref> He is perhaps best known for producing \"[[Pedestrian (Gunna song)|Pedestrian]]\" by rapper [[Gunna (rapper)|Gunna]], as well as \"[[Lost It (Rich the Kid song)|Lost It]]\" by rapper [[Rich The Kid]] featuring [[Offset (rapper)|Offset]] and [[Quavo]] of [[Migos]] which was [[certified gold]] by the [[RIAA]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&se=rich+the+kid+lost+it#search_section|title=Gold & Platinum - RIAA|publisher=[[RIAA]]|accessdate=December 26, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"RTK\">{{cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2018/03/rich-the-kid-the-world-is-yours-album-production-credits/|title=Production Credits for Rich The Kid's 'The World Is Yours' Album|publisher=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]|accessdate=December 26, 2018}}</ref>\n\nDoughboy has [[hip hop production|produced]] several tracks for various artists such as [[Young Jeezy]], [[Gucci Mane]], [[Future (rapper)|Future]], [[Yo Gotti]], [[Juicy J]], [[21 Savage]], [[YoungBoy Never Broke Again|NBA Youngboy]], [[Lil Boosie]], [[Soulja Boy]], [[Shy Glizzy]], [[YFN Lucci]], [[Plies (rapper)|Plies]], [[Trina]], [[Crooked I]], [[B.G. (rapper)|B.G]], [[CyHi the Prynce]], among others.<ref name=\"DBG\">{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/artists/Doughboy-beatz|title=Doughboy Beatz on Genius|publisher=|accessdate=December 26, 2018}}</ref> He has earned a [[Grammy Nomination]] for his work on 21 Savage's ''[[I Am Greater than I Was|I Am > I Was]]'' for [[Grammy Award for Best Rap Album|Best Rap Album]] at the [[62nd Annual Grammy Awards]].\n\n==Early Life and Career==\nBrandon started making beats at the age of 15, for his younger brother on [[FL Studio]].<ref name=\"DBG\"/> He then went on to produce [[Hitz Committee]]/[[Jive Records]] signee, Trai'D's lead single \"Gutta Chick\" in 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://djbooth.net/songs/traid-gutta-chick |title=Trai'D - Gutta Chick |publisher=DJBbooth.net |date=|accessdate=December 26, 2018}}</ref> \"Gutta Chick\" peaked at number 72 on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] charts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/traid/chart-history/r-b-hip-hop-songs/song/540786 |title=Trai'D Chart History |publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=|accessdate=December 26, 2018}}</ref>  Doughboy has worked with many other major artists since then.\n\nThroughout the 2010s, Doughboy has followed up with production on many highly acclaimed projects that include [[Jeezy]]'s ''[[Trap or Die 2]]'', [[Shy Glizzy]]'s ''Law 3'', [[Rich The Kid]]'s ''[[The World Is Yours (Rich the Kid album)|The World Is Yours]]'', [[Gunna (rapper)|Gunna]]'s ''[[Drip Season 3]]'' and [[Gucci Mane]]'s ''[[East Atlanta Santa]]''.\n\nBrandon has also worked with other music producers that include [[Metro Boomin]], [[Wheezy (record producer)|Wheezy]], [[Drumma Boy]], [[Southside (record producer)|Southside]], [[Zaytoven]], [[Shawty Redd]], [[Sonny Digital]], [[Honorable C.N.O.T.E.]], [[DJ Paul]], [[Juicy J]] and more.\n\nIn September 2019, Doughboy signed with [[Metro Boomin]]'s Boominati Worldwide label.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MetroBoomin/status/1174728677206233090 |title=Metro Boomin on Twitter |publisher=[[Twitter]] |date=|accessdate=October 7, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/BoominatiWW/status/1174813473051688965 |title=Boominati Worldwide on Twitter |publisher=[[Twitter]] |date=|accessdate=October 7, 2019}}</ref>   Boominati Worldwide has a partnership with [[Republic Records]] and [[Universal Music Group]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/7849328/metro-boomin-boominati-worldwide-label-bryson-tiller-tour |title=Metro Boomin Launches Boominati Worldwide Label, Joins Bryson Tiller on Set It Off Tour |publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=|accessdate=October 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n=== Studio albums ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\